Dorkly, while I do understand why someone would make this mistake, it is a common misconception that all ghost type Pokémon are dead. They are not technically dead, but original members of a ghost type species, for example the very first gastly, do take some soul from another organism to come into being. However, there are other ways a ghost type pokemon can form, like breeding, or just evolution. This means that while they may appear to be, they are not always dead organisms.
